  "response": "Here are the key differences between death metal and black metal:\n\nDeath Metal:\n- Focuses on heavy, technical instrumentation\n- Growled, guttural vocal style\n- Typically themes of violence, gore, and death\n- More straightforward musical structure\n- Originated in the mid-1980s in the US and Europe\n- Emphasizes complex guitar riffs and percussion\n\nBlack Metal:\n- Characterized by high-pitched, shrieking vocals\n- Often features raw, lo-fi production\n- Themes of darkness, paganism, nature, and anti-Christianity\n- More atmospheric and melodic\n- Originated in Norway in the early 1990s\n- Typically uses tremolo picking and blast beat drumming\n- Often incorporates symphonic or folk elements\n\nBoth are extreme metal subgenres with intense, aggressive sounds, but they have distinct musical and thematic characteristics.",
